{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775836666913,"sessionID":"ses_287e323f0ffeRSHYr3i6L0TFAl","part":{"id":"prt_d781d17b6001gWgk49w0TKvmxl","messageID":"msg_d781d0d80001KQAcWYAvJshtWX","sessionID":"ses_287e323f0ffeRSHYr3i6L0TFAl","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_d9c19e59be8a4086bd1f1809","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-014/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-014/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-014 вҖ” Valkey Storage Implementation вҖ” Design\n2: \n3: ## 1. Architecture\n4: \n5: ### 1.1 Purpose\n6: \n7: This document specifies the Valkey backend implementation for the `pkg/store` session storage module in AgentCube. It provides a concrete `Store` interface implementation using `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`, persisting sandbox metadata as JSON strings and maintaining sorted-set indices for garbage collection workflows.\n8: \n9: ### 1.2 Valkey Data Architecture\n10: \n11: ```\n12: в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\n13: в”Ӯ                    valkeyStore                          в”Ӯ\n14: в”Ӯ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ  в”Ӯ\n15: в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  cli: valkey.Client                               в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ\n16: в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  sessionPrefix:        \"session:\"                 в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ\n17: в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  expiryIndexKey:       \"session:expiry\"           в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ\n18: в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  lastActivityIndexKey: \"session:last_activity\"    в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ\n19: в”Ӯ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ  в”Ӯ\n20: в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n21:                         в”Ӯ\n22:                         в–ј\n23: в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\n24: в”Ӯ                      Valkey Server                      в”Ӯ\n25: в”Ӯ                                                         в”Ӯ\n26: в”Ӯ  String Keys:                                           в”Ӯ\n27: в”Ӯ    session:{sessionID} вҶ’ JSON(SandboxInfo)              в”Ӯ\n28: в”Ӯ                                                         в”Ӯ\n29: в”Ӯ  Sorted Sets:                                           в”Ӯ\n30: в”Ӯ    session:expiry          ZSET { sessionID: score }    в”Ӯ\n31: в”Ӯ      score = ExpiresAt.Unix()                           в”Ӯ\n32: в”Ӯ                                                         в”Ӯ\n33: в”Ӯ    session:last_activity   ZSET { sessionID: score }    в”Ӯ\n34: в”Ӯ      score = lastActivityAt.Unix()                      в”Ӯ\n35: в”Ӯ                                                         в”Ӯ\n36: в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n37: ```\n38: \n39: ### 1.3 Package Layout\n40: \n41: ```\n42: pkg/store/\n43: в”ңв”Җв”Җ store.go                  # Store interface (shared)\n44: в”ңв”Җв”Җ singleton.go              # Provider selection (shared)\n45: в”ңв”Җв”Җ store_valkey.go           # Valkey implementation вҶҗ AR-014\n46: в”ңв”Җв”Җ store_valkey_test.go      # Valkey unit tests вҶҗ AR-014\n47: в””в”Җв”Җ codec.go                  # JSON encode/decode helpers (shared)\n48: ```\n49: \n50: ### 1.4 Dependencies\n51: \n52: | Module | Version | Purpose |\n53: |--------|---------|---------|\n54: | `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | latest | Valkey client library |\n55: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | вҖ” | `SandboxInfo` type |\n56: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | v2.130.1 | Structured logging |\n57: \n58: ---\n59: \n60: ## 2. Data Model\n61: \n62: ### 2.1 Valkey Store Struct\n63: \n64: ```go\n65: type valkeyStore struct {\n66:     cli                  valkey.Client\n67:     sessionPrefix        string\n68:     expiryIndexKey       string\n69:     lastActivityIndexKey string\n70: }\n71: ```\n72: \n73: ### 2.2 Key Constants\n74: \n75: | Constant | Value | Purpose |\n76: |----------|-------|---------|\n77: | `sessionPrefix` | `\"session:\"` | Prefix for session JSON string keys |\n78: | `expiryIndexKey` | `\"session:expiry\"` | ZSET for expiry-based GC queries |\n79: | `lastActivityIndexKey` | `\"session:last_activity\"` | ZSET for activity-based GC queries |\n80: \n81: ### 2.3 Valkey Key Patterns\n82: \n83: | Key Pattern | Type | Content |\n84: |-------------|------|---------|\n85: | `session:{sessionID}` | String | JSON-marshaled `SandboxInfo` |\n86: | `session:expiry` | Sorted Set | Member: `sessionID`, Score: `ExpiresAt.Unix()` |\n87: | `session:last_activity` | Sorted Set | Member: `sessionID`, Score: `LastActivityAt.Unix()` |\n88: \n89: ### 2.4 SandboxInfo JSON Schema\n90: \n91: Identical to AR-013 Redis implementation. Stored as JSON string at `session:{sessionID}`.\n92: \n93: ### 2.5 Sorted Set Score Semantics\n94: \n95: | Index | Score Source | When Written |\n96: |-------|-------------|--------------|\n97: | `session:expiry` | `float64(ExpiresAt.Unix())` | `StoreSandbox` |\n98: | `session:last_activity` | `float64(time.Now().Unix())` | `StoreSandbox` |\n99: | `session:last_activity` | `float64(at.Unix())` or `time.Now()` | `UpdateSessionLastActivity` |\n100: \n101: ---\n102: \n103: ## 3. Interfaces\n104: \n105: ### 3.1 Store Interface Implementation\n106: \n107: `valkeyStore` implements the same `Store` interface as `redisStore`:\n108: \n109: ```go\n110: type Store interface {\n111:     Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n112:     GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n113:     StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n114:     UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n115:     DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n116:     ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n117:     ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n118:     UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n119:     Close() error\n120: }\n121: ```\n122: \n123: ### 3.2 Method Specifications\n124: \n125: Method specifications are identical to AR-013 Redis implementation, with Valkey-specific command mappings:\n126: \n127: | Redis Command | Valkey Equivalent | Notes |\n128: |---------------|-------------------|-------|\n129: | `PING` | `PING` | Same |\n130: | `GET` | `GET` | Same |\n131: | `SETNX` | `SET NX` | Same semantics |\n132: | `SET XX` | `SET XX` | Same semantics |\n133: | `DEL` | `DEL` | Same |\n134: | `ZADD` | `ZADD` | Same |\n135: | `ZREM` | `ZREM` | Same |\n136: | `ZRANGEBYSCORE` | `ZRANGEBYSCORE` | Same |\n137: | `MGET` | `MGET` | Same |\n138: | `EXISTS` | `EXISTS` | Same |\n139: \n140: ### 3.3 Constructor\n141: \n142: ```go\n143: func newValkeyStore() (*valkeyStore, error) {\n144:     valkeyAddr := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_ADDR\")\n145:     if valkeyAddr == \"\" {\n146:         return nil, errors.New(\"VALKEY_ADDR is required\")\n147:     }\n148: \n149:     valkeyPassword := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD\")\n150:     passwordRequired := strings.ToLower(os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\"))\n151:     if valkeyPassword == \"\" && passwordRequired != \"false\" {\n152:         return nil, errors.New(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD is required (set VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false to disable)\")\n153:     }\n154: \n155:     cli, err := valkey.NewClient(valkey.ClientOption{InitAddress: []string{valkeyAddr}, Password: valkeyPassword})\n156:     if err != nil {\n157:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"valkey client creation failed: %w\", err)\n158:     }\n159: \n160:     if err := cli.Do(context.Background(), cli.B().Ping().Build()).Error(); err != nil {\n161:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"valkey ping failed: %w\", err)\n162:     }\n163: \n164:     return &valkeyStore{\n165:         cli:                  cli,\n166:         sessionPrefix:        \"session:\",\n167:         expiryIndexKey:       \"session:expiry\",\n168:         lastActivityIndexKey: \"session:last_activity\",\n169:     }, nil\n170: }\n171: ```\n172: \n173: ### 3.4 Environment Variables\n174: \n175: | Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n176: |----------|----------|---------|-------|\n177: | `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes | вҖ” | Valkey server address |\n178: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Yes* | вҖ” | Auth password |\n179: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Case-insensitive `\"false\"` disables |\n180: | `STORE_TYPE` | No | `redis` | Must be `valkey` for this backend |\n181: \n182: ---\n183: \n184: ## 4. Error Handling\n185: \n186: Identical to AR-013 Redis implementation. Valkey client errors propagate with context.\n187: \n188: ---\n189: \n190: ## 5. Testing Strategy\n191: \n192: ### 5.1 Unit Test Matrix\n193: \n194: Test cases mirror AR-013 Redis tests with Valkey-specific setup:\n195: \n196: | Test Name | Description | Assertions |\n197: |-----------|-------------|------------|\n198: | `TestValkeyStore_Ping_Success` | PING вҶ’ PONG | `require.NoError` |\n199: | `TestValkeyStore_Ping_Failure` | Bad connection | `assert.Error` |\n200: | `TestValkeyStore_GetSandboxBySessionID_Found` | Store then get | `assert.Equal` on SessionID |\n201: | `TestValkeyStore_GetSandboxBySessionID_NotFound` | Missing key | `assert.ErrorIs(ErrNotFound)` |\n202: | `TestValkeyStore_StoreSandbox_Success` | Full pipeline | Key exists, ZSET members added |\n203: | `TestValkeyStore_StoreSandbox_NilRejected` | nil input | `assert.Error` |\n204: | `TestValkeyStore_StoreSandbox_ZeroExpiry` | Zero ExpiresAt | `assert.Error` |\n205: | `TestValkeyStore_StoreSandbox_Idempotent` | Double store | Second call doesn't overwrite |\n206: | `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSandbox_Success` | SETXX updates | JSON changed, ZSET unchanged |\n207: | `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSandbox_MissingKey` | No prior store | `assert.Error` contains \"key not exists\" |\n208: | `TestValkeyStore_DeleteSandboxBySessionID` | Full cleanup | Key deleted, ZSET members removed |\n209: | `TestValkeyStore_ListExpiredSandboxes` | Query by expiry | Returns expired, not active |\n210: | `TestValkeyStore_ListExpiredSandboxes_ZeroLimit` | limit=0 | Returns `nil, nil` |\n211: | `TestValkeyStore_ListExpiredSandboxes_OrphanMember` | ZSET member without key | Skipped, not error |\n212: | `TestValkeyStore_ListInactiveSandboxes` | Query by activity | Returns inactive, not active |\n213: | `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity_Success` | Valid session | ZADD with new score |\n214: | `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity_NotFound` | Missing session | `assert.ErrorIs(ErrNotFound)` |\n215: | `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity_ZeroTime` | `at.IsZero()` | Uses `time.Now()` |\n216: | `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity_EmptyID` | Empty sessionID | `assert.Error` |\n217: | `TestValkeyStore_Close` | Connection closed | No error |\n218: \n219: ### 5.2 Gate Requirements\n220: \n221: 1. `go build ./pkg/store/...` compiles\n222: 2. `go test ./pkg/store/... -v` all pass\n223: 3. `go test -race ./pkg/store/...` no data race warnings\n224: 4. No `log.Printf` usage (use klog)\n225: 5. No sensitive data in logs (passwords, connection strings)\n226: 6. Test coverage вүҘ 80% for `store_valkey.go`\n227: \n228: ---\n229: \n230: ## 6. Deployment Considerations\n231: \n232: ### 6.1 Connection Pooling\n233: \n234: valkey-go uses its own connection pooling. Default settings should suffice for initial deployment.\n235: \n236: ### 6.2 Password Policy\n237: \n238: Password required by default. Set `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` only in trusted network environments.\n239: \n240: ### 6.3 ZSET Index Growth\n241: \n242: Identical to Redis implementation. GC controller must regularly clean up expired/inactive sessions.\n243: \n244: ### 6.4 Memory Considerations\n245: \n246: Identical to Redis implementation: ~700 bytes Г— number of active sessions.\n247: \n248: ### 6.5 Valkey Cluster\n249: \n250: For Valkey Cluster deployments:\n251: - Consider hash tags for key slot affinity: `session:{cluster}:{sessionID}`\n252: - `MGET` in `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` requires keys in same slot\n253: - Monitor `CROSSSLOT` errors\n254: \n255: ---\n256: \n257: ## 7. Implementation Steps\n258: \n259: ### Phase 1: Core Implementation (Day 1)\n260: \n261: 1. Implement `valkeyStore` struct in `store_valkey.go`\n262: 2. Implement constructor with environment variable validation\n263: 3. Implement `Ping`, `Close`, `sessionKey` helper\n264: \n265: ### Phase 2: CRUD Operations (Day 2)\n266: \n267: 1. Implement `StoreSandbox` with pipeline\n268: 2. Implement `UpdateSandbox` with SET XX\n269: 3. Implement `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` with pipeline\n270: 4. Implement `GetSandboxBySessionID` with ErrNotFound handling\n271: \n272: ### Phase 3: Query Operations (Day 3)\n273: \n274: 1. Implement `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` helper\n275: 2. Implement `ListExpiredSandboxes`\n276: 3. Implement `ListInactiveSandboxes`\n277: 4. Implement `UpdateSessionLastActivity`\n278: \n279: ### Phase 4: Testing & Validation (Day 4)\n280: \n281: 1. Write unit tests\n282: 2. Run `go test -race ./pkg/store/...`\n283: 3. Verify test coverage\n284: 4. Fix all issues\n285: \n286: ---\n287: \n288: ## 8. Future Changes\n289: \n290: | Change | Description | Priority |\n291: |--------|-------------|----------|\n292: | AR-0XX | TTL on session keys for automatic cleanup | P1 |\n293: | AR-0XX | Hash tag support for Valkey Cluster slot affinity | P2 |\n294: | AR-0XX | Metrics: store operation latency, error rates | P2 |\n295: \n296: ### Known Limitations\n297: \n298: - No automatic TTL on session JSON keys; relies on GC controller for cleanup\n299: - `MGET` in `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` assumes single-slot keys for cluster deployments\n300: - No pagination for `List*` methods beyond simple `limit` parameter\n301: - `SET NX` in `StoreSandbox` prevents updates; use `UpdateSandbox` for modifications\n\n(End of file - total 301 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-014 вҖ” Valkey Storage Implementation вҖ” Design\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Purpose\n\nThis document specifies the Valkey backend implementation for the `pkg/store` session storage module in AgentCube. It provides a concrete `Store` interface implementation using `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`, persisting sandbox metadata as JSON strings and maintaining sorted-set indices for garbage collection workflows.\n\n### 1.2 Valkey Data Architecture\n\n```\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ                    valkeyStore                          в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  cli: valkey.Client                               в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  sessionPrefix:        \"session:\"                 в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  expiryIndexKey:       \"session:expiry\"           в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  lastActivityIndexKey: \"session:last_activity\"    в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ  в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-014/design.md","time":{"start":1775836666903,"end":1775836666911}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775836668140,"sessionID":"ses_287e323f0ffeRSHYr3i6L0TFAl","part":{"id":"prt_d781d1cec001y5HKtQTsa65bWg","messageID":"msg_d781d0d80001KQAcWYAvJshtWX","sessionID":"ses_287e323f0ffeRSHYr3i6L0TFAl","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_9234c0238f0d4ceaa932c91e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/store/store.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/store/store.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package store\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \t\"context\"\n5: \t\"errors\"\n6: \t\"time\"\n7: \n8: \t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n9: \t\"k8s.io/klog/v2\"\n10: )\n11: \n12: var ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"sandbox not found\")\n13: \n14: type Store interface {\n15: \tStoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, info *types.SandboxInfo) error\n16: \tUpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, info *types.SandboxInfo) error\n17: \tDeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n18: \tGetSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n19: \tListSandboxes(ctx context.Context) (map[string]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n20: \tUpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n21: \n22: \tListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n23: \tListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n24: \tPing(ctx context.Context) error\n25: \tClose() error\n26: }\n27: \n28: func Storage() Store {\n29: \tinitStoreOnce.Do(func() {\n30: \t\tif err := initStore(); err != nil {\n31: \t\t\tklog.Fatalf(\"init store failed: %v\", err)\n32: \t\t}\n33: \t})\n34: \treturn storeInstance\n35: }\n\n(End of file - total 35 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package store\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"errors\"\n\t\"time\"\n\n\t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n\t\"k8s.io/klog/v2\"\n)\n\nvar ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"sandbox not found\")\n\ntype Store interface {\n\tStoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, info *types.SandboxInfo) error\n\tUpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, info *types.SandboxInfo) error\n\tDeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n\tGetSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n\tListSandboxes(ctx context.Context) (map[string]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n\tUpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/store/store.go","time":{"start":1775836668122,"end":1775836668138}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775836669431,"sessionID":"ses_287e323f0ffeRSHYr3i6L0TFAl","part":{"id":"prt_d781d21c80012qh9TkEbrt5nFh","messageID":"msg_d781d0d80001KQAcWYAvJshtWX","sessionID":"ses_287e323f0ffeRSHYr3i6L0TFAl","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_9ad993351ac3401c9effa9a5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/store/store_valkey.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/store/store_valkey.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package store\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \t\"context\"\n5: \t\"errors\"\n6: \t\"fmt\"\n7: \t\"os\"\n8: \t\"strconv\"\n9: \t\"strings\"\n10: \t\"time\"\n11: \n12: \tvalkey \"github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go\"\n13: \t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n14: )\n15: \n16: type valkeyStore struct {\n17: \tcli                  valkey.Client\n18: \tsessionPrefix        string\n19: \texpiryIndexKey       string\n20: \tlastActivityIndexKey string\n21: }\n22: \n23: func newValkeyStore() (Store, error) {\n24: \taddr := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_ADDR\")\n25: \tif addr == \"\" {\n26: \t\treturn nil, errors.New(\"VALKEY_ADDR is required\")\n27: \t}\n28: \n29: \taddresses := strings.Split(addr, \",\")\n30: \tfor i := range addresses {\n31: \t\taddresses[i] = strings.TrimSpace(addresses[i])\n32: \t}\n33: \n34: \tpassword := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD\")\n35: \tpasswordRequired := strings.ToLower(os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\"))\n36: \tif password == \"\" && passwordRequired != \"false\" {\n37: \t\treturn nil, errors.New(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD is required (set VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false to disable)\")\n38: \t}\n39: \n40: \tdisableCache := strings.ToLower(os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE\")) == \"true\"\n41: \tforceSingle := strings.ToLower(os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE\")) == \"true\"\n42: \n43: \tclient, err := valkey.NewClient(valkey.ClientOption{\n44: \t\tInitAddress:       addresses,\n45: \t\tPassword:          password,\n46: \t\tDisableCache:      disableCache,\n47: \t\tForceSingleClient: forceSingle,\n48: \t})\n49: \tif err != nil {\n50: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create valkey client: %w\", err)\n51: \t}\n52: \n53: \treturn &valkeyStore{\n54: \t\tcli:                  client,\n55: \t\tsessionPrefix:        \"session:\",\n56: \t\texpiryIndexKey:       \"session:expiry\",\n57: \t\tlastActivityIndexKey: \"session:last_activity\",\n58: \t}, nil\n59: }\n60: \n61: func (v *valkeyStore) Ping(ctx context.Context) error {\n62: \tresp, err := v.cli.Do(ctx, v.cli.B().Ping().Build()).ToString()\n63: \tif err != nil {\n64: \t\treturn err\n65: \t}\n66: \tif resp != \"PONG\" {\n67: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"unexpected ping response: %s\", resp)\n68: \t}\n69: \treturn nil\n70: }\n71: \n72: func (v *valkeyStore) GetSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n73: \tkey := v.sessionKey(sessionID)\n74: \tdata, err := v.cli.Do(ctx, v.cli.B().Get().Key(key).Build()).ToString()\n75: \tif valkey.IsValkeyNil(err) {\n76: \t\treturn nil, ErrNotFound\n77: \t}\n78: \tif err != nil {\n79: \t\treturn nil, err\n80: \t}\n81: \treturn decodeSandboxInfo([]byte(data))\n82: }\n83: \n84: func (v *valkeyStore) StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, info *types.SandboxInfo) error {\n85: \tif info == nil {\n86: \t\treturn errors.New(\"sandbox is nil\")\n87: \t}\n88: \tif info.ExpiresAt.IsZero() {\n89: \t\treturn errors.New(\"sandbox ExpiresAt is zero\")\n90: \t}\n91: \n92: \tdata, err := encodeSandboxInfo(info)\n93: \tif err != nil {\n94: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"marshal sandbox: %w\", err)\n95: \t}\n96: \n97: \tkey := v.sessionKey(sessionID)\n98: \tnow := float64(time.Now().Unix())\n99: \texpiryScore := float64(info.ExpiresAt.Unix())\n100: \n101: \tresults := v.cli.DoMulti(ctx,\n102: \t\tv.cli.B().Setnx().Key(key).Value(string(data)).Build(),\n103: \t\tv.cli.B().Zadd().Key(v.expiryIndexKey).ScoreMember().ScoreMember(expiryScore, sessionID).Build(),\n104: \t\tv.cli.B().Zadd().Key(v.lastActivityIndexKey).ScoreMember().ScoreMember(now, sessionID).Build(),\n105: \t)\n106: \n107: \tfor _, result := range results {\n108: \t\tif err := result.Error(); err != nil {\n109: \t\t\treturn err\n110: \t\t}\n111: \t}\n112: \treturn nil\n113: }\n114: \n115: func (v *valkeyStore) UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, info *types.SandboxInfo) error {\n116: \tif info == nil {\n117: \t\treturn errors.New(\"sandbox is nil\")\n118: \t}\n119: \n120: \tdata, err := encodeSandboxInfo(info)\n121: \tif err != nil {\n122: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"marshal sandbox: %w\", err)\n123: \t}\n124: \n125: \tkey := v.sessionKey(sessionID)\n126: \tresp, err := v.cli.Do(ctx, v.cli.B().Set().Key(key).Value(string(data)).Xx().Build()).ToString()\n127: \tif err != nil {\n128: \t\treturn err\n129: \t}\n130: \tif resp != \"OK\" {\n131: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"key not exists: %s\", key)\n132: \t}\n133: \treturn nil\n134: }\n135: \n136: func (v *valkeyStore) DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error {\n137: \tresults := v.cli.DoMulti(ctx,\n138: \t\tv.cli.B().Del().Key(v.sessionPrefix+sessionID).Build(),\n139: \t\tv.cli.B().Zrem().Key(v.expiryIndexKey).Member(sessionID).Build(),\n140: \t\tv.cli.B().Zrem().Key(v.lastActivityIndexKey).Member(sessionID).Build(),\n141: \t)\n142: \n143: \tfor _, result := range results {\n144: \t\tif err := result.Error(); err != nil {\n145: \t\t\treturn err\n146: \t\t}\n147: \t}\n148: \treturn nil\n149: }\n150: \n151: func (v *valkeyStore) ListSandboxes(ctx context.Context) (map[string]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n152: \tsessionIDs, err := v.cli.Do(ctx, v.cli.B().Zrange().Key(v.expiryIndexKey).Min(\"0\").Max(\"-1\").Build()).AsStrSlice()\n153: \tif err != nil {\n154: \t\treturn nil, err\n155: \t}\n156: \n157: \tresult := make(map[string]*types.SandboxInfo)\n158: \tfor _, id := range sessionIDs {\n159: \t\tinfo, err := v.GetSandbox(ctx, id)\n160: \t\tif err != nil {\n161: \t\t\tif err == ErrNotFound {\n162: \t\t\t\tcontinue\n163: \t\t\t}\n164: \t\t\treturn nil, err\n165: \t\t}\n166: \t\tresult[id] = info\n167: \t}\n168: \n169: \treturn result, nil\n170: }\n171: \n172: func (v *valkeyStore) UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error {\n173: \tif sessionID == \"\" {\n174: \t\treturn errors.New(\"sessionID is empty\")\n175: \t}\n176: \n177: \tif at.IsZero() {\n178: \t\tat = time.Now()\n179: \t}\n180: \n181: \tkey := v.sessionKey(sessionID)\n182: \texists, err := v.cli.Do(ctx, v.cli.B().Exists().Key(key).Build()).AsInt64()\n183: \tif err != nil {\n184: \t\treturn err\n185: \t}\n186: \tif exists == 0 {\n187: \t\treturn ErrNotFound\n188: \t}\n189: \n190: \tscore := float64(at.Unix())\n191: \treturn v.cli.Do(ctx, v.cli.B().Zadd().Key(v.lastActivityIndexKey).ScoreMember().ScoreMember(score, sessionID).Build()).Error()\n192: }\n193: \n194: func (v *valkeyStore) ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n195: \tif limit <= 0 {\n196: \t\treturn nil, nil\n197: \t}\n198: \n199: \tmaxScore := strconv.FormatInt(before.Unix(), 10)\n200: \tsessionIDs, err := v.cli.Do(ctx, v.cli.B().Zrangebyscore().Key(v.expiryIndexKey).Min(\"-inf\").Max(maxScore).Limit(0, int64(limit)).Build()).AsStrSlice()\n201: \tif err != nil {\n202: \t\treturn nil, err\n203: \t}\n204: \n205: \tvar result []*types.SandboxInfo\n206: \tfor _, id := range sessionIDs {\n207: \t\tinfo, err := v.GetSandbox(ctx, id)\n208: \t\tif err != nil {\n209: \t\t\tif err == ErrNotFound {\n210: \t\t\t\tcontinue\n211: \t\t\t}\n212: \t\t\treturn nil, err\n213: \t\t}\n214: \t\tresult = append(result, info)\n215: \t}\n216: \n217: \treturn result, nil\n218: }\n219: \n220: func (v *valkeyStore) ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n221: \tif limit <= 0 {\n222: \t\treturn nil, nil\n223: \t}\n224: \n225: \tmaxScore := strconv.FormatInt(before.Unix(), 10)\n226: \tsessionIDs, err := v.cli.Do(ctx, v.cli.B().Zrangebyscore().Key(v.lastActivityIndexKey).Min(\"-inf\").Max(maxScore).Limit(0, int64(limit)).Build()).AsStrSlice()\n227: \tif err != nil {\n228: \t\treturn nil, err\n229: \t}\n230: \n231: \tvar result []*types.SandboxInfo\n232: \tfor _, id := range sessionIDs {\n233: \t\tinfo, err := v.GetSandbox(ctx, id)\n234: \t\tif err != nil {\n235: \t\t\tif err == ErrNotFound {\n236: \t\t\t\tcontinue\n237: \t\t\t}\n238: \t\t\treturn nil, err\n239: \t\t}\n240: \t\tresult = append(result, info)\n241: \t}\n242: \n243: \treturn result, nil\n244: }\n245: \n246: func (v *valkeyStore) sessionKey(sessionID string) string {\n247: \treturn v.sessionPrefix + sessionID\n248: }\n249: \n250: func (v *valkeyStore) Close() error {\n251: \tv.cli.Close()\n252: \treturn nil\n253: }\n\n(End of file - total 253 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package store\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"errors\"\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"os\"\n\t\"strconv\"\n\t\"strings\"\n\t\"time\"\n\n\tvalkey \"github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go\"\n\t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n)\n\ntype valkeyStore struct {\n\tcli                  valkey.Client\n\tsessionPrefix        string\n\texpiryIndexKey       string\n\tlastActivityIndexKey string","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/store/store_valkey.go","time":{"start":1775836669418,"end":1775836669429}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775836670651,"sessionID":"ses_287e323f0ffeRSHYr3i6L0TFAl","part":{"id":"prt_d781d2682001YhiBx9u7C8JGyP","messageID":"msg_d781d0d80001KQAcWYAvJshtWX","sessionID":"ses_287e323f0ffeRSHYr3i6L0TFAl","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_c1a5ce00d23f4abb955d2d89","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/store/store_redis.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/store/store_redis.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package store\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \t\"context\"\n5: \t\"errors\"\n6: \t\"fmt\"\n7: \t\"os\"\n8: \t\"strconv\"\n9: \t\"strings\"\n10: \t\"time\"\n11: \n12: \t\"github.com/redis/go-redis/v9\"\n13: \t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n14: )\n15: \n16: type redisStore struct {\n17: \tcli                  redis.UniversalClient\n18: \tsessionPrefix        string\n19: \texpiryIndexKey       string\n20: \tlastActivityIndexKey string\n21: }\n22: \n23: func newRedisStore() (Store, error) {\n24: \taddr := os.Getenv(\"REDIS_ADDR\")\n25: \tif addr == \"\" {\n26: \t\treturn nil, errors.New(\"REDIS_ADDR is required\")\n27: \t}\n28: \n29: \tpassword := os.Getenv(\"REDIS_PASSWORD\")\n30: \tpasswordRequired := strings.ToLower(os.Getenv(\"REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\"))\n31: \tif password == \"\" && passwordRequired != \"false\" {\n32: \t\treturn nil, errors.New(\"REDIS_PASSWORD is required (set REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false to disable)\")\n33: \t}\n34: \n35: \topts := &redis.Options{\n36: \t\tAddr:     addr,\n37: \t\tPassword: password,\n38: \t}\n39: \n40: \tcli := redis.NewClient(opts)\n41: \n42: \treturn &redisStore{\n43: \t\tcli:                  cli,\n44: \t\tsessionPrefix:        \"session:\",\n45: \t\texpiryIndexKey:       \"session:expiry\",\n46: \t\tlastActivityIndexKey: \"session:last_activity\",\n47: \t}, nil\n48: }\n49: \n50: func (r *redisStore) Ping(ctx context.Context) error {\n51: \tpong, err := r.cli.Ping(ctx).Result()\n52: \tif err != nil {\n53: \t\treturn err\n54: \t}\n55: \tif pong != \"PONG\" {\n56: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"unexpected ping response: %s\", pong)\n57: \t}\n58: \treturn nil\n59: }\n60: \n61: func (r *redisStore) GetSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n62: \tkey := r.sessionKey(sessionID)\n63: \tdata, err := r.cli.Get(ctx, key).Bytes()\n64: \tif err == redis.Nil {\n65: \t\treturn nil, ErrNotFound\n66: \t}\n67: \tif err != nil {\n68: \t\treturn nil, err\n69: \t}\n70: \treturn decodeSandboxInfo(data)\n71: }\n72: \n73: func (r *redisStore) StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, info *types.SandboxInfo) error {\n74: \tif info == nil {\n75: \t\treturn errors.New(\"sandbox is nil\")\n76: \t}\n77: \tif info.ExpiresAt.IsZero() {\n78: \t\treturn errors.New(\"sandbox ExpiresAt is zero\")\n79: \t}\n80: \n81: \tdata, err := encodeSandboxInfo(info)\n82: \tif err != nil {\n83: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"marshal sandbox: %w\", err)\n84: \t}\n85: \n86: \tkey := r.sessionKey(sessionID)\n87: \tnow := float64(time.Now().Unix())\n88: \texpiryScore := float64(info.ExpiresAt.Unix())\n89: \n90: \tpipe := r.cli.Pipeline()\n91: \tpipe.SetNX(ctx, key, data, 0)\n92: \tpipe.ZAdd(ctx, r.expiryIndexKey, redis.Z{Score: expiryScore, Member: sessionID})\n93: \tpipe.ZAdd(ctx, r.lastActivityIndexKey, redis.Z{Score: now, Member: sessionID})\n94: \n95: \t_, err = pipe.Exec(ctx)\n96: \treturn err\n97: }\n98: \n99: func (r *redisStore) UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, info *types.SandboxInfo) error {\n100: \tif info == nil {\n101: \t\treturn errors.New(\"sandbox is nil\")\n102: \t}\n103: \n104: \tdata, err := encodeSandboxInfo(info)\n105: \tif err != nil {\n106: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"marshal sandbox: %w\", err)\n107: \t}\n108: \n109: \tkey := r.sessionKey(sessionID)\n110: \tok, err := r.cli.SetXX(ctx, key, data, 0).Result()\n111: \tif err != nil {\n112: \t\treturn err\n113: \t}\n114: \tif !ok {\n115: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"key not exists: %s\", key)\n116: \t}\n117: \treturn nil\n118: }\n119: \n120: func (r *redisStore) DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error {\n121: \tkey := r.sessionKey(sessionID)\n122: \n123: \tpipe := r.cli.Pipeline()\n124: \tpipe.Del(ctx, key)\n125: \tpipe.ZRem(ctx, r.expiryIndexKey, sessionID)\n126: \tpipe.ZRem(ctx, r.lastActivityIndexKey, sessionID)\n127: \n128: \t_, err := pipe.Exec(ctx)\n129: \treturn err\n130: }\n131: \n132: func (r *redisStore) ListSandboxes(ctx context.Context) (map[string]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n133: \tsessionIDs, err := r.cli.ZRange(ctx, r.expiryIndexKey, 0, -1).Result()\n134: \tif err != nil {\n135: \t\treturn nil, err\n136: \t}\n137: \n138: \treturn r.loadSandboxesBySessionIDsAsMap(ctx, sessionIDs)\n139: }\n140: \n141: func (r *redisStore) loadSandboxesBySessionIDsAsMap(ctx context.Context, sessionIDs []string) (map[string]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n142: \tif len(sessionIDs) == 0 {\n143: \t\treturn make(map[string]*types.SandboxInfo), nil\n144: \t}\n145: \n146: \tkeys := make([]string, len(sessionIDs))\n147: \tfor i, id := range sessionIDs {\n148: \t\tkeys[i] = r.sessionKey(id)\n149: \t}\n150: \n151: \tresults, err := r.cli.MGet(ctx, keys...).Result()\n152: \tif err != nil {\n153: \t\treturn nil, err\n154: \t}\n155: \n156: \tresult := make(map[string]*types.SandboxInfo)\n157: \tfor i, raw := range results {\n158: \t\tif raw == nil {\n159: \t\t\tcontinue\n160: \t\t}\n161: \t\tdata, ok := raw.(string)\n162: \t\tif !ok || data == \"\" {\n163: \t\t\tcontinue\n164: \t\t}\n165: \t\tinfo, err := decodeSandboxInfo([]byte(data))\n166: \t\tif err != nil {\n167: \t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"unmarshal sandbox: %w\", err)\n168: \t\t}\n169: \t\tresult[sessionIDs[i]] = info\n170: \t}\n171: \treturn result, nil\n172: }\n173: \n174: func (r *redisStore) UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error {\n175: \tif sessionID == \"\" {\n176: \t\treturn errors.New(\"sessionID is empty\")\n177: \t}\n178: \tif at.IsZero() {\n179: \t\tat = time.Now()\n180: \t}\n181: \n182: \tkey := r.sessionKey(sessionID)\n183: \texists, err := r.cli.Exists(ctx, key).Result()\n184: \tif err != nil {\n185: \t\treturn err\n186: \t}\n187: \tif exists == 0 {\n188: \t\treturn ErrNotFound\n189: \t}\n190: \n191: \treturn r.cli.ZAdd(ctx, r.lastActivityIndexKey, redis.Z{\n192: \t\tScore:  float64(at.Unix()),\n193: \t\tMember: sessionID,\n194: \t}).Err()\n195: }\n196: \n197: func (r *redisStore) ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n198: \tif limit <= 0 {\n199: \t\treturn nil, nil\n200: \t}\n201: \n202: \tmaxScore := strconv.FormatInt(before.Unix(), 10)\n203: \tsessionIDs, err := r.cli.ZRangeByScore(ctx, r.expiryIndexKey, &redis.ZRangeBy{\n204: \t\tMin:    \"-inf\",\n205: \t\tMax:    maxScore,\n206: \t\tOffset: 0,\n207: \t\tCount:  int64(limit),\n208: \t}).Result()\n209: \tif err != nil {\n210: \t\treturn nil, err\n211: \t}\n212: \n213: \treturn r.loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx, sessionIDs)\n214: }\n215: \n216: func (r *redisStore) ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n217: \tif limit <= 0 {\n218: \t\treturn nil, nil\n219: \t}\n220: \n221: \tmaxScore := strconv.FormatInt(before.Unix(), 10)\n222: \tsessionIDs, err := r.cli.ZRangeByScore(ctx, r.lastActivityIndexKey, &redis.ZRangeBy{\n223: \t\tMin:    \"-inf\",\n224: \t\tMax:    maxScore,\n225: \t\tOffset: 0,\n226: \t\tCount:  int64(limit),\n227: \t}).Result()\n228: \tif err != nil {\n229: \t\treturn nil, err\n230: \t}\n231: \n232: \treturn r.loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx, sessionIDs)\n233: }\n234: \n235: func (r *redisStore) loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx context.Context, sessionIDs []string) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n236: \tif len(sessionIDs) == 0 {\n237: \t\treturn nil, nil\n238: \t}\n239: \n240: \tkeys := make([]string, len(sessionIDs))\n241: \tfor i, id := range sessionIDs {\n242: \t\tkeys[i] = r.sessionKey(id)\n243: \t}\n244: \n245: \tresults, err := r.cli.MGet(ctx, keys...).Result()\n246: \tif err != nil {\n247: \t\treturn nil, err\n248: \t}\n249: \n250: \tvar sandboxes []*types.SandboxInfo\n251: \tfor _, raw := range results {\n252: \t\tif raw == nil {\n253: \t\t\tcontinue\n254: \t\t}\n255: \t\tdata, ok := raw.(string)\n256: \t\tif !ok || data == \"\" {\n257: \t\t\tcontinue\n258: \t\t}\n259: \t\tinfo, err := decodeSandboxInfo([]byte(data))\n260: \t\tif err != nil {\n261: \t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"unmarshal sandbox: %w\", err)\n262: \t\t}\n263: \t\tsandboxes = append(sandboxes, info)\n264: \t}\n265: \treturn sandboxes, nil\n266: }\n267: \n268: func (r *redisStore) sessionKey(sessionID string) string {\n269: \treturn r.sessionPrefix + sessionID\n270: }\n271: \n272: func (r *redisStore) Close() error {\n273: \treturn r.cli.Close()\n274: }\n\n(End of file - total 274 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package store\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"errors\"\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"os\"\n\t\"strconv\"\n\t\"strings\"\n\t\"time\"\n\n\t\"github.com/redis/go-redis/v9\"\n\t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n)\n\ntype redisStore struct {\n\tcli                  redis.UniversalClient\n\tsessionPrefix        string\n\texpiryIndexKey       string\n\tlastActivityIndexKey string","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/store/store_redis.go","time":{"start":1775836670642,"end":1775836670650}}}}
