{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775836830023,"sessionID":"ses_287e323f0ffeRSHYr3i6L0TFAl","part":{"id":"prt_d781dd46a001v9674CpV2Cpluz","messageID":"msg_d781db1d4001h0Wk7wJ9GroBXR","sessionID":"ses_287e323f0ffeRSHYr3i6L0TFAl","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_7d451b9620474b8696133450","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-014 вҖ” Valkey Storage Implementation вҖ” Design\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Purpose\n\nThis document specifies the Valkey backend implementation for the `pkg/store` session storage module in AgentCube. It provides a concrete `Store` interface implementation using `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`, persisting sandbox metadata as JSON strings and maintaining sorted-set indices for garbage collection workflows.\n\n### 1.2 Valkey Data Architecture\n\n```\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ                    valkeyStore                          в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  cli: valkey.Client                               в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  sessionPrefix:        \"session:\"                 в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  expiryIndexKey:       \"session:expiry\"           в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  lastActivityIndexKey: \"session:last_activity\"    в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ  в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n                        в”Ӯ\n                        в–ј\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ                      Valkey Server                      в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ                                                         в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  String Keys:                                           в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ    session:{sessionID} вҶ’ JSON(SandboxInfo)              в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ                                                         в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  Sorted Sets:                                           в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ    session:expiry          ZSET { sessionID: score }    в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ      score = ExpiresAt.Unix()                           в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ                                                         в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ    session:last_activity   ZSET { sessionID: score }    в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ      score = time.Now().Unix() (on store)               в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ                                                         в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n```\n\n### 1.3 Package Layout\n\n```\npkg/store/\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ store.go                  # Store interface (shared)\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ singleton.go              # Provider selection (shared)\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ store_valkey.go           # Valkey implementation вҶҗ AR-014\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ store_valkey_test.go      # Valkey unit tests вҶҗ AR-014\nв””в”Җв”Җ codec.go                  # JSON encode/decode helpers (shared)\n```\n\n### 1.4 Dependencies\n\n| Module | Version | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | latest | Valkey client library |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | вҖ” | `SandboxInfo` type alias |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/handler` | вҖ” | `SandboxInfo` struct definition |\n\n---\n\n## 2. Data Model\n\n### 2.1 Valkey Store Struct\n\n```go\ntype valkeyStore struct {\n    cli                  valkey.Client\n    sessionPrefix        string\n    expiryIndexKey       string\n    lastActivityIndexKey string\n}\n```\n\n### 2.2 Key Constants\n\n| Constant | Value | Purpose |\n|----------|-------|---------|\n| `sessionPrefix` | `\"session:\"` | Prefix for session JSON string keys |\n| `expiryIndexKey` | `\"session:expiry\"` | ZSET for expiry-based GC queries |\n| `lastActivityIndexKey` | `\"session:last_activity\"` | ZSET for activity-based GC queries |\n\n### 2.3 Valkey Key Patterns\n\n| Key Pattern | Type | Content |\n|-------------|------|---------|\n| `session:{sessionID}` | String | JSON-marshaled `SandboxInfo` |\n| `session:expiry` | Sorted Set | Member: `sessionID`, Score: `ExpiresAt.Unix()` |\n| `session:last_activity` | Sorted Set | Member: `sessionID`, Score: `time.Now().Unix()` |\n\n### 2.4 SandboxInfo JSON Schema\n\nStored as JSON string at `session:{sessionID}`:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"sessionId\": \"session-abc-123\",\n  \"sandboxName\": \"sandbox-name\",\n  \"sandboxId\": \"uuid-string\",\n  \"workloadName\": \"agent-runtime\",\n  \"namespace\": \"default\",\n  \"kind\": \"AgentRuntime\",\n  \"podIp\": \"10.0.0.1\",\n  \"entryPoints\": [\n    {\n      \"path\": \"/api\",\n      \"protocol\": \"http\",\n      \"endpoint\": \"http://10.0.0.1:8080\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-10T07:00:00Z\",\n  \"expiresAt\": \"2026-04-10T08:00:00Z\",\n  \"status\": \"running\",\n  \"lastActivityAt\": \"2026-04-10T07:05:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\n### 2.5 Sorted Set Score Semantics\n\n| Index | Score Source | When Written |\n|-------|-------------|--------------|\n| `session:expiry` | `float64(ExpiresAt.Unix())` | `StoreSandbox` |\n| `session:last_activity` | `float64(time.Now().Unix())` | `StoreSandbox` |\n| `session:last_activity` | `float64(at.Unix())` or `time.Now()` | `UpdateSessionLastActivity` |\n\n---\n\n## 3. Interfaces\n\n### 3.1 Store Interface\n\n`valkeyStore` implements the shared `Store` interface defined in `store.go`:\n\n```go\ntype Store interface {\n    StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, info *types.SandboxInfo) error\n    UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, info *types.SandboxInfo) error\n    DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n    GetSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    ListSandboxes(ctx context.Context) (map[string]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n    ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n    Close() error\n}\n```\n\n### 3.2 Method Specifications\n\n#### 3.2.1 Ping\n\n| Aspect | Detail |\n|--------|--------|\n| Valkey Command | `B().Ping().Build()` via `Do()` |\n| Success | Response string equals `\"PONG\"` |\n| Error | Connection error propagated |\n\n```go\nfunc (v *valkeyStore) Ping(ctx context.Context) error {\n    resp, err := v.cli.Do(ctx, v.cli.B().Ping().Build()).ToString()\n    if err != nil {\n        return err\n    }\n    if resp != \"PONG\" {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"unexpected ping response: %s\", resp)\n    }\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n#### 3.2.2 GetSandbox\n\n| Aspect | Detail |\n|--------|--------|\n| Key | `session:{sessionID}` |\n| Valkey Command | `B().Get().Key(key).Build()` |\n| Not Found | `valkey.IsValkeyNil(err)` вҶ’ `ErrNotFound` |\n| Success | JSON unmarshal via `decodeSandboxInfo()` |\n\n```go\nfunc (v *valkeyStore) GetSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n    key := v.sessionKey(sessionID)\n    data, err := v.cli.Do(ctx, v.cli.B().Get().Key(key).Build()).ToString()\n    if valkey.IsValkeyNil(err) {\n        return nil, ErrNotFound\n    }\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n    return decodeSandboxInfo([]byte(data))\n}\n```\n\n#### 3.2.3 StoreSandbox\n\n| Aspect | Detail |\n|--------|--------|\n| Validation | Reject nil sandbox; reject zero `ExpiresAt` |\n| Valkey Commands | `DoMulti`: `SETNX`, `ZADD` (expiry), `ZADD` (activity) |\n| Atomicity | Commands sent in single `DoMulti` call; each result checked for errors |\n| Idempotency | `SETNX` prevents overwriting existing session |\n\n```go\nfunc (v *valkeyStore) StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, info *types.SandboxInfo) error {\n    if info == nil {\n        return errors.New(\"sandbox is nil\")\n    }\n    if info.ExpiresAt.IsZero() {\n        return errors.New(\"sandbox ExpiresAt is zero\")\n    }\n\n    data, err := encodeSandboxInfo(info)\n    if err != nil {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"marshal sandbox: %w\", err)\n    }\n\n    key := v.sessionKey(sessionID)\n    now := float64(time.Now().Unix())\n    expiryScore := float64(info.ExpiresAt.Unix())\n\n    results := v.cli.DoMulti(ctx,\n        v.cli.B().Setnx().Key(key).Value(string(data)).Build(),\n        v.cli.B().Zadd().Key(v.expiryIndexKey).ScoreMember().ScoreMember(expiryScore, sessionID).Build(),\n        v.cli.B().Zadd().Key(v.lastActivityIndexKey).ScoreMember().ScoreMember(now, sessionID).Build(),\n    )\n\n    for _, result := range results {\n        if err := result.Error(); err != nil {\n            return err\n        }\n    }\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n#### 3.2.4 UpdateSandbox\n\n| Aspect | Detail |\n|--------|--------|\n| Valkey Command | `B().Set().Key(key).Value(data).Xx().Build()` |\n| Not Found | Response != `\"OK\"` вҶ’ `fmt.Errorf(\"key not exists: %s\", key)` |\n| Side Effects | Does NOT modify ZSET entries |\n\n```go\nfunc (v *valkeyStore) UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, info *types.SandboxInfo) error {\n    if info == nil {\n        return errors.New(\"sandbox is nil\")\n    }\n\n    data, err := encodeSandboxInfo(info)\n    if err != nil {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"marshal sandbox: %w\", err)\n    }\n\n    key := v.sessionKey(sessionID)\n    resp, err := v.cli.Do(ctx, v.cli.B().Set().Key(key).Value(string(data)).Xx().Build()).ToString()\n    if err != nil {\n        return err\n    }\n    if resp != \"OK\" {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"key not exists: %s\", key)\n    }\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n#### 3.2.5 DeleteSandboxBySessionID\n\n| Aspect | Detail |\n|--------|--------|\n| Valkey Commands | `DoMulti`: `DEL`, `ZREM` (expiry), `ZREM` (activity) |\n| Atomicity | All commands in single `DoMulti` call |\n\n```go\nfunc (v *valkeyStore) DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error {\n    results := v.cli.DoMulti(ctx,\n        v.cli.B().Del().Key(v.sessionPrefix+sessionID).Build(),\n        v.cli.B().Zrem().Key(v.expiryIndexKey).Member(sessionID).Build(),\n        v.cli.B().Zrem().Key(v.lastActivityIndexKey).Member(sessionID).Build(),\n    )\n\n    for _, result := range results {\n        if err := result.Error(); err != nil {\n            return err\n        }\n    }\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n#### 3.2.6 ListSandboxes\n\n| Aspect | Detail |\n|--------|--------|\n| Valkey Command | `B().Zrange().Key(expiryIndexKey).Min(\"0\").Max(\"-1\").Build()` |\n| Follow-up | Individual `GetSandbox` calls per session ID |\n| Missing Keys | Orphan ZSET members skipped (not errors) |\n| Return Type | `map[string]*types.SandboxInfo` keyed by session ID |\n\n```go\nfunc (v *valkeyStore) ListSandboxes(ctx context.Context) (map[string]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n    sessionIDs, err := v.cli.Do(ctx, v.cli.B().Zrange().Key(v.expiryIndexKey).Min(\"0\").Max(\"-1\").Build()).AsStrSlice()\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n\n    result := make(map[string]*types.SandboxInfo)\n    for _, id := range sessionIDs {\n        info, err := v.GetSandbox(ctx, id)\n        if err != nil {\n            if err == ErrNotFound {\n                continue\n            }\n            return nil, err\n        }\n        result[id] = info\n    }\n\n    return result, nil\n}\n```\n\n#### 3.2.7 ListExpiredSandboxes\n\n| Aspect | Detail |\n|--------|--------|\n| Precondition | `limit <= 0` вҶ’ return `nil, nil` |\n| Valkey Command | `B().Zrangebyscore().Key(expiryIndexKey).Min(\"-inf\").Max(maxScore).Limit(0, limit).Build()` |\n| Follow-up | Individual `GetSandbox` calls per session ID |\n| Missing Keys | Orphan ZSET members skipped |\n| Return Type | `[]*types.SandboxInfo` slice |\n\n```go\nfunc (v *valkeyStore) ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n    if limit <= 0 {\n        return nil, nil\n    }\n\n    maxScore := strconv.FormatInt(before.Unix(), 10)\n    sessionIDs, err := v.cli.Do(ctx, v.cli.B().Zrangebyscore().Key(v.expiryIndexKey).Min(\"-inf\").Max(maxScore).Limit(0, int64(limit)).Build()).AsStrSlice()\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n\n    var result []*types.SandboxInfo\n    for _, id := range sessionIDs {\n        info, err := v.GetSandbox(ctx, id)\n        if err != nil {\n            if err == ErrNotFound {\n                continue\n            }\n            return nil, err\n        }\n        result = append(result, info)\n    }\n\n    return result, nil\n}\n```\n\n#### 3.2.8 ListInactiveSandboxes\n\n| Aspect | Detail |\n|--------|--------|\n| Same as ListExpiredSandboxes | Queries `session:last_activity` ZSET |\n\n```go\nfunc (v *valkeyStore) ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n    if limit <= 0 {\n        return nil, nil\n    }\n\n    maxScore := strconv.FormatInt(before.Unix(), 10)\n    sessionIDs, err := v.cli.Do(ctx, v.cli.B().Zrangebyscore().Key(v.lastActivityIndexKey).Min(\"-inf\").Max(maxScore).Limit(0, int64(limit)).Build()).AsStrSlice()\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n\n    var result []*types.SandboxInfo\n    for _, id := range sessionIDs {\n        info, err := v.GetSandbox(ctx, id)\n        if err != nil {\n            if err == ErrNotFound {\n                continue\n            }\n            return nil, err\n        }\n        result = append(result, info)\n    }\n\n    return result, nil\n}\n```\n\n#### 3.2.9 UpdateSessionLastActivity\n\n| Aspect | Detail |\n|--------|--------|\n| Validation | Reject empty `sessionID` |\n| Zero Time | If `at.IsZero()`, use `time.Now()` |\n| Precondition | Session key must exist; absent вҶ’ `ErrNotFound` |\n| Valkey Commands | `EXISTS` вҶ’ `ZADD session:last_activity` |\n\n```go\nfunc (v *valkeyStore) UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error {\n    if sessionID == \"\" {\n        return errors.New(\"sessionID is empty\")\n    }\n\n    if at.IsZero() {\n        at = time.Now()\n    }\n\n    key := v.sessionKey(sessionID)\n    exists, err := v.cli.Do(ctx, v.cli.B().Exists().Key(key).Build()).AsInt64()\n    if err != nil {\n        return err\n    }\n    if exists == 0 {\n        return ErrNotFound\n    }\n\n    score := float64(at.Unix())\n    return v.cli.Do(ctx, v.cli.B().Zadd().Key(v.lastActivityIndexKey).ScoreMember().ScoreMember(score, sessionID).Build()).Error()\n}\n```\n\n#### 3.2.10 Close\n\n```go\nfunc (v *valkeyStore) Close() error {\n    v.cli.Close()\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n### 3.3 Helper Functions\n\n#### 3.3.1 sessionKey\n\n```go\nfunc (v *valkeyStore) sessionKey(sessionID string) string {\n    return v.sessionPrefix + sessionID\n}\n```\n\n### 3.4 Constructor\n\n```go\nfunc newValkeyStore() (Store, error) {\n    addr := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_ADDR\")\n    if addr == \"\" {\n        return nil, errors.New(\"VALKEY_ADDR is required\")\n    }\n\n    addresses := strings.Split(addr, \",\")\n    for i := range addresses {\n        addresses[i] = strings.TrimSpace(addresses[i])\n    }\n\n    password := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD\")\n    passwordRequired := strings.ToLower(os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\"))\n    if password == \"\" && passwordRequired != \"false\" {\n        return nil, errors.New(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD is required (set VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false to disable)\")\n    }\n\n    disableCache := strings.ToLower(os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE\")) == \"true\"\n    forceSingle := strings.ToLower(os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE\")) == \"true\"\n\n    client, err := valkey.NewClient(valkey.ClientOption{\n        InitAddress:       addresses,\n        Password:          password,\n        DisableCache:      disableCache,\n        ForceSingleClient: forceSingle,\n    })\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create valkey client: %w\", err)\n    }\n\n    return &valkeyStore{\n        cli:                  client,\n        sessionPrefix:        \"session:\",\n        expiryIndexKey:       \"session:expiry\",\n        lastActivityIndexKey: \"session:last_activity\",\n    }, nil\n}\n```\n\nNote: Constructor does NOT perform a ping check. Connection validation occurs lazily on first operation.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Error Handling\n\n### 4.1 Error Types\n\n| Error | Source | Handling |\n|-------|--------|----------|\n| `ErrNotFound` | Package sentinel (`store.go`) | Returned when session key absent |\n| `valkey.IsValkeyNil(err)` | valkey-go | Normalized to `ErrNotFound` in `GetSandbox` |\n| `DoMulti` result errors | Individual command errors | First error returned, batch aborts |\n| Validation errors | Input checks | Descriptive `errors.New()` messages |\n| Connection errors | Valkey client | Propagated with context |\n\n### 4.2 Error Handling Matrix\n\n| Scenario | Error Returned | Notes |\n|----------|---------------|-------|\n| Session key not found | `ErrNotFound` | `valkey.IsValkeyNil` normalized |\n| Nil sandbox to StoreSandbox | `errors.New(\"sandbox is nil\")` | Input validation |\n| Zero ExpiresAt | `errors.New(\"sandbox ExpiresAt is zero\")` | Input validation |\n| Empty sessionID | `errors.New(\"sessionID is empty\")` | UpdateSessionLastActivity |\n| UpdateSandbox missing key | `fmt.Errorf(\"key not exists: %s\", key)` | SET XX returns non-OK |\n| Missing VALKEY_ADDR | `errors.New(\"VALKEY_ADDR is required\")` | Constructor |\n| Missing VALKEY_PASSWORD | `errors.New(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD is required ...\")` | Unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` |\n| Client creation failure | `fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create valkey client: %w\", err)` | Constructor |\n\n### 4.3 Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------|\n| `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes | вҖ” | Comma-separated addresses; split and trimmed |\n| `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Yes* | вҖ” | Auth password |\n| `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Case-insensitive `\"false\"` disables |\n| `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | `false` | Case-insensitive `\"true\"` enables `DisableCache` |\n| `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | `false` | Case-insensitive `\"true\"` enables `ForceSingleClient` |\n| `STORE_TYPE` | No | `redis` | Must be `valkey` for this backend |\n\n---\n\n## 5. Testing Strategy\n\n### 5.1 Unit Test Matrix\n\nValkey tests use mock `valkeyStore` structs (no in-memory Valkey server equivalent to miniredis). Tests cover validation logic, error paths, and structural correctness:\n\n| Test Name | Description | Assertions |\n|-----------|-------------|------------|\n| `TestValkeyStore_StoreSandbox_NilInfo` | nil sandbox input | `assert.Contains(\"sandbox is nil\")` |\n| `TestValkeyStore_StoreSandbox_ZeroExpiry` | Zero `ExpiresAt` | `assert.Contains(\"ExpiresAt is zero\")` |\n| `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSandbox_NilInfo` | nil sandbox input | `assert.Contains(\"sandbox is nil\")` |\n| `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity_EmptySessionID` | Empty sessionID | `assert.Contains(\"sessionID is empty\")` |\n| `TestValkeyStore_ListExpiredSandboxes_LimitZero` | limit=0 | Returns `nil, nil` |\n| `TestValkeyStore_ListExpiredSandboxes_LimitNegative` | limit=-5 | Returns `nil, nil` |\n| `TestValkeyStore_ListInactiveSandboxes_LimitZero` | limit=0 | Returns `nil, nil` |\n| `TestValkeyStore_ListInactiveSandboxes_LimitNegative` | limit=-1 | Returns `nil, nil` |\n| `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity_ZeroTime` | `at.IsZero()` logic | Verifies `time.Now()` substitution |\n| `TestValkeyStore_ListExpiredSandboxes_ScoreCalculation` | Score for 1hr ago | `assert.Equal(int64(-3600))` |\n| `TestValkeyStore_ListInactiveSandboxes_ScoreCalculation` | Score for 2hr ago | `assert.Equal(int64(-7200))` |\n| `TestValkeyStore_StructFields` | Constant values | Field assertions |\n| `TestValkeyStore_InterfaceCompliance` | Compile-time check | `var _ Store = (*valkeyStore)(nil)` |\n| `TestNewValkeyStore_MissingAddr` | No `VALKEY_ADDR` | `assert.Contains(\"VALKEY_ADDR is required\")` |\n| `TestNewValkeyStore_MissingPassword` | No password, required | `assert.Contains(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD is required\")` |\n| `TestNewValkeyStore_PasswordNotRequired` | `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` | `require.NoError`, `require.NotNil` |\n| `TestNewValkeyStore_PasswordRequiredTrue` | `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=true` | `assert.Contains(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD is required\")` |\n\n### 5.2 Test Limitations\n\nUnlike the Redis tests which use `miniredis` for full integration testing, Valkey tests are limited to:\n- Input validation (nil checks, zero checks, empty checks)\n- Constructor environment variable parsing\n- Score calculation verification\n- Interface compliance compile-time checks\n- Struct field value assertions\n\nFull integration tests requiring a live Valkey server are not included.\n\n### 5.3 Gate Requirements\n\n1. `go build ./pkg/store/...` compiles\n2. `go test ./pkg/store/... -v` all pass\n3. `go test -race ./pkg/store/...` no data race warnings\n4. No `log.Printf` usage (use klog)\n5. No sensitive data in logs (passwords, connection strings)\n6. Test coverage вүҘ 80% for `store_valkey.go`\n\n---\n\n## 6. Deployment Considerations\n\n### 6.1 Connection Pooling\n\nvalkey-go manages its own connection pooling internally. Default settings should suffice for initial deployment. `ForceSingleClient` option available via `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=true` for non-cluster setups.\n\n### 6.2 Password Policy\n\nPassword required by default. Set `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` only in trusted network environments.\n\n### 6.3 ZSET Index Growth\n\n`session:expiry` and `session:last_activity` sorted sets grow monotonically. Ensure the GC controller regularly calls:\n- `ListExpiredSandboxes` вҶ’ `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`\n- `ListInactiveSandboxes` вҶ’ `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`\n\n### 6.4 Memory Considerations\n\n- Session JSON strings: ~500 bytes per sandbox\n- ZSET entries: ~100 bytes per session ID per index\n- Estimated memory: ~700 bytes Г— number of active sessions\n\n### 6.5 Valkey Cluster\n\nFor Valkey Cluster deployments:\n- Consider hash tags for key slot affinity: `session:{cluster}:{sessionID}`\n- `ListSandboxes` iterates with individual GET calls (not MGET), avoiding CROSSSLOT issues\n- Monitor for cross-slot errors if future optimizations use MGET\n\n### 6.6 Cache and Client Options\n\n- `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true`: Disables client-side response caching\n- `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=true`: Forces single-client mode even with multiple addresses\n\n---\n\n## 7. Implementation Steps\n\n### Phase 1: Core Implementation (Day 1)\n\n1. Implement `valkeyStore` struct in `store_valkey.go`\n2. Implement constructor with environment variable validation\n3. Implement `Ping`, `Close`, `sessionKey` helper\n\n### Phase 2: CRUD Operations (Day 2)\n\n1. Implement `StoreSandbox` with `DoMulti`\n2. Implement `UpdateSandbox` with SET XX\n3. Implement `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` with `DoMulti`\n4. Implement `GetSandbox` with `ErrNotFound` handling\n\n### Phase 3: Query Operations (Day 3)\n\n1. Implement `ListSandboxes` with ZRANGE + individual GETs\n2. Implement `ListExpiredSandboxes` with ZRANGEBYSCORE\n3. Implement `ListInactiveSandboxes` with ZRANGEBYSCORE\n4. Implement `UpdateSessionLastActivity`\n\n### Phase 4: Testing & Validation (Day 4)\n\n1. Write unit tests (validation + constructor)\n2. Run `go test -race ./pkg/store/...`\n3. Verify test coverage\n4. Fix all issues\n\n---\n\n## 8. Future Changes\n\n| Change | Description | Priority |\n|--------|-------------|----------|\n| AR-0XX | TTL on session keys for automatic cleanup | P1 |\n| AR-0XX | Hash tag support for Valkey Cluster slot affinity | P2 |\n| AR-0XX | Metrics: store operation latency, error rates | P2 |\n| AR-0XX | Integration tests with testcontainers-valkey | P2 |\n| AR-0XX | MGET optimization for batch loads (with hash tags) | P3 |\n\n### Known Limitations\n\n- No automatic TTL on session JSON keys; relies on GC controller for cleanup\n- `ListSandboxes` and `List*` methods use individual GET calls instead of MGET; less efficient for large batches\n- No pagination for `List*` methods beyond simple `limit` parameter\n- `SETNX` in `StoreSandbox` prevents updates; use `UpdateSandbox` for modifications\n- No in-memory Valkey mock for integration testing; tests limited to validation logic\n- Constructor does not ping server; connection errors surface on first operation\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-014/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/reconciler.go\">\nERROR [78:24] cannot use (func() literal) (value of type func()) as func(interface{}) value in argument to runtime.HandleCrash\nERROR [83:24] cannot use (func() literal) (value of type func()) as func(interface{}) value in argument to runtime.HandleCrash\nERROR [88:24] cannot use (func() literal) (value of type func()) as func(interface{}) value in argument to runtime.HandleCrash\nERROR [97:24] cannot use (func() literal) (value of type func()) as func(interface{}) value in argument to runtime.HandleCrash\nERROR [102:24] cannot use (func() literal) (value of type func()) as func(interface{}) value in argument to runtime.HandleCrash\nERROR 